<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/714> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #714" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Defeated the Aurunci and vowed a temple to Juno Moneta (Liv. 7.28.2-6). See Degrassi 106, 406f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/713> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #713" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Furius, see Act. Tr. on 338; on that of Manlius, see Fast. Cap. on 359. Degrassi (105, on 350) is inclined to identify Furius with the Dictator of 350 and Consul of 349, but Münzer with RE no. 42, the Consul of 338 and 325." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/695> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #695" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.24.11; Fast. Cap. (see note 1); Cic. Sen. 41; Chr. 354 (Camello et Crasso); Fast. Hyd. (Camillo et Crasso), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f. The aged Claudius died in office (Liv. 7.25.10). Camillus successfully fought the Gauls in Latium (see Tribunes of the Soldiers), but could not come to grips with Greek pirates (Liv. 7.25-26; Claud. Quad., fr. 12 Peter; Dion. Hal. 15.1; Frontin. Str. 2.6.1; App. Celt. 1.2; Eutrop. 2.6; Auct. Vir. Ill. 29; cf. Polyb. 2.18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/694> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #694" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Furius was a son of the hero Camillus. Of Claudius' name Fast. Cap. preserves: [Ap. Cl]audius P. f. A[p. n. Crass., I]nrigil[lens(is)]." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/691> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #691" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to hold elections, through which two patricians attained the consulship of 349 (Liv. 7.24.11, and 25.1). See Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/690> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #690" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Furius was a son of the hero Camillus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/539> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #539" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Left in charge of the camp by his father, the Dictator (Plut. Cam. 35.1)." .
